In response to the message sent      Wed, 17 Jul 85 9:45:27 BST from robert@UCL-CS.ARPA

Robert,

What ICMP message did you use to pry the gateway routing tables from
the gateway? Presumably EGP could be used to do this, but this method
would have the rest of the world believe you are a gateway. Personally,
I believe something like this an appropriate thing to ask a gateway,
but this view is not a popular one in the BBN community. I have
suggested an ICMP request/response pair that would return information
(hop count, etc.) about a network upon request. Something we should
put on the agenda for the GADS meeting.

Dave
